    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential crash in nr_pdcp_reconfigure_srb due to invalid t_Reordering values\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_pdcp_reconfigure_srb()` function could crash when called with invalid encoded t_Reordering values. This change adds proper bounds checking and error handling to prevent crashes and provide better diagnostic information.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/nr_pdcp/nr_pdcp_oai_api.c`: Added bounds validation for t_Reordering parameter, improved error logging, and fixed type casting issues. Also added missing header inclusion for configuration definitions.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen the function is called with out-of-range encoded t_Reordering values (e.g., negative numbers or values >= 37), the decode_t_reordering function would previously assert and terminate the program. With this fix, the function now gracefully handles these cases by logging an error and returning without crashing.\n\nUsers may observe segfaults or unexpected termination when reconfiguring SRBs with invalid t_Reordering parameters. After this fix, such cases will result in error log messages indicating the valid range instead of program termination.\n\n"
}